<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>Lee E. Landes and his wife Sue founded Mothers Against Drunk Driving (MADD) of southeast Michigan in 1982, after losing their son in "an alcohol related accident" (Argus-Press, Owosso, Michigan, 9/15/82). Landes served as spokesman for the local chapter of MADD and then as Michigan State Director of MADD in the mid 1980s.</p>
</bioghist>



<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>The Landes collection includes organizational records, correspondence, promotional materials, and legal records of the national board, as well as materials from the Michigan and Texas chapters.</p>
</scopecontent>

